8.10.20  4:43 am   Is perfection only searched for with songs and videos or has it plagued other parts of your life?

      perfection is useful, but it's not that good by itself. perfection is nothing. emptiness. empty void. if there is anything else, any pattern or marking of any kind to disturb it, then it's clearly not perfect, because you could ask 'why is the mark here, and not there.' the only way it could be unquestionably perfect is if there were no discernable figure or pattern anywhere, like if the whole thing is totally blank, shapeless, sizeless, and nothing. this does not plague me, and i don't search for it. i don't know where you heard that
